      "writtenOn": "2017-07-27T14:57:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we have a lot of tests for handlers. We should probably change that. \nAny problems in the handlers show up very quickly and most often they are in one of the lower level packages. Which usually results in revising the tests there. \nIMO it\u0027s ok to keep the test on handlers light until there is an issue that suggests more automated tests, but I defer to Walter if he has a different opinion. \n\nHere is an example I found https://elithrar.github.io/article/testing-http-handlers-go/\nthat looks like a good approach.",
